cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.SE, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DB (Database): The paper discusses specialized Time Series Management Systems (TSMSs) developed to overcome the limitations of general purpose Database Management Systems (DBMSs) for times series management. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the functionality for storage and querying of time series data implemented by various TSMSs. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the capabilities of TSMSs with regard to Stream Processing and Approximate Query Processing (AQP), which are relevant to information retrieval. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper provides an overview of each TSMS with a focus on the motivational use case that drove the development of the system and the components the system is composed of, which are relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions enormous distributed Cyber-Physical Systems (CPSs) producing large volumes of data at high velocity, which suggests a potential relevance to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing.
